<p>&ldquo;His suggestions for securing the U.S.-Mexico border went beyond walls to include moats, fiery moats and fiery moats with fire-proof crocodiles.&rdquo; (<a href="http://www.editorandpublisher.com/eandp/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1002613019">source</a>)</p>
<p>Fire-proof crocodiles are expensive.  Wouldn't ut be easier to have TWO parallel moats, one filled with crocodiles, and another one filled with fire?</p>

